A Nigerian female student shares a video as she calls the world for help after facing racism and discrimination in University Of Saskatchewan In Canada. Gistvic Reports. She wrote: “I am a black graduate Student at the University of Saskatchewan, Canada and I am calling on the world. I have experienced racism and discrimination to a suicidal level. This has been the case for most black people in a certain department of the Institution.” WATCH VIDEO BELOW: I am a black graduate Student at the University of Saskatchewan, Canada and I am calling on the world. I have experienced racism and discrimination to a suicidal level. This has been the case for most black people in a certain department of the Institution. Please share & help! pic.twitter.com/KeNh1YVnlc Source: gistvic.com